***This inclusive employer is a member of myGwork – the largest global platform for the LGBTQ+ business community.***
 The Transaction Advisory (TA) team is part of Marsh’s global Private Equity and Mergers & Acquisitions (PEMA) Practice. The TA team draws from Marsh’s in-depth global knowledge to deliver specialist services to the private equity, corporate, infrastructure, and alternative asset management industries. We work with clients during the lifecycle of an investment, advising on risk and insurance matters at acquisition; during the hold phase; and at exit. Our global PEMA practice consists of more than 220 professionals based worldwide and the Nordic PEMA practice consists of close to 20 professionals based in Stockholm, Copenhagen and Oslo.




 The Nordic TA team is one of the leading insurance and risk advisory teams in the market. Given that our Nordic-based private capital client community routinely invests in European / global companies, you can expect to regularly interact with our established network of colleagues across the world. This global network is consistently recognised by our clients as a key strength.




 Marsh is seeking candidates for the following position based in the Stockholm office:




**Transaction Advisory (TA) Project Manager**
 The TA project manager role involves analyzing a vast number of different businesses from an insurance and risk perspective as well as coordinating input from various specialists across the Marsh business and presenting these findings in a coherent way to our clients. Given that the majority of our interactions are with executive-level managers or board members, you will quickly learn polished communication and presentation skills which are invaluable to any role. Additionally, the broad knowledge you will build (and relationships you will form) through your interaction with other teams in the Marsh (and wider Marsh McLennan) business provides ample opportunity to learn about other Marsh McLennan businesses and grow your career. Finally, with our clients raising ever-larger funds which need to be invested, the TA team remains on a strong growth trajectory which presents opportunities within the TA team itself.




**What can you expect?**
* You will be providing insurance advice to clients. The team works with Private Equity, Infrastructure and Corporate clients throughout the lifecycle of their investments, advising on risk and insurance matters and solutions.
* The team provides pre-acquisition (and pre-divestment) insurance due diligence services. They advise clients on the insurance and risk profile of the companies the clients are seeking to acquire (or divest). The team also acts as an introducer for other Marsh services, such as cyber advisory and transactional risk insurances.
* You will manage due diligence projects (often several at a time).
* You will be operating in a diverse, client facing position where a mixture of technical insurance, excellent communication and organisation skills will be required.


**What’s in it for you?**
* The opportunity to join a fast moving, fast growing successful operation within Marsh;
* A team that strives to deliver best practice, market-leading service and solutions with a focus on client service excellence;
* Excellent training and development with ongoing career opportunities;
* A creative, commercially focused role;
* Comprehensive benefits programs including: pension contributions, private health insurance, volunteer opportunities, and other programs.


**We Will Count On You To**
* Understand deal-specific requirements of clients, including the nature of target businesses;
* Negotiate commercial terms of engagement and issue engagement documentation;
* Assess the robustness of target company insurance programs and associated costs;
* Draw on the knowledge of colleagues across Marsh to support this assessment;
* Deliver findings to clients in a formal report format, typically supplemented by calls and/or meetings;
* Build strong working relationships with clients to support business growth;
* Identify opportunities to offer other Marsh McLennan services which would be valuable to clients.


**What You Need To Have**
* Strong technical insurance experience, gained working for an insurer or insurance broker;
* A strong understanding of Property & Casualty, Liability and Financial Lines insurance programmes would be advantageous;
* Knowledge and experience of global insurance programs (or working with global clients) would be highly beneficial;
* Prior experience of providing advisory services to the M&A community would also be beneficial (but not essential);
* English proficiency, both verbal and written.


**What Makes You Stand Out**
* Property & Casualty experience;
* Current private equity / M&A exposure within insurance;
* A desire to challenge yourself in the fast-paced, demanding and rewarding world of M&A.


**If you are interested,** 
**we would love to hear from you. Please submit your application in English.**
 Marsh is the world’s leading insurance broker and risk adviser. With more than 45,000 colleagues operating in more than 130 countries, Marsh serves commercial and individual clients with data driven risk solutions and advisory services. Marsh is a business of Marsh McLennan (NYSE: MMC), the leading global professional services firm in the areas of risk, strategy and people. With annual revenue of over $20 billion, Marsh McLennan helps clients navigate an increasingly dynamic and complex environment through four market-leading businesses: Marsh, Guy Carpenter, Mercer, and Oliver Wyman. For more information, visit marshmclennan.com, follow us on LinkedIn and Twitter.




 Marsh McLennan is committed to embracing a diverse, inclusive and flexible work environment. We aim to attract and retain the best people and embrace diversity of age background, civil partnership status, disability, ethnic origin, family duties, gender orientation or expression, gender reassignment, marital status, nationality, parental status, personal or social status, political affiliation, race, religion and beliefs, sex/gender, sexual orientation or expression, skin color, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law. We are an equal opportunities employer. We are committed to providing reasonable adjustments in accordance with applicable law to any candidate with a disability to allow them to fully participate in the recruitment process. If you have a disability that may require reasonable adjustments, please contact us at TAUK@mmc.com.




 Marsh McLennan is committed to hybrid work, which includes the flexibility of working remotely and the collaboration, connections and professional development benefits of working together in the office. All Marsh McLennan colleagues are expected to be in their local based teams will identify at least one “anchor day” per week on which their full team will be together in person. office or working onsite with clients at least three days per week. Office-based teams will identify at least one “anchor day” per week on which their full team will be together in person.

The team of experts providing analytical services to healthcare clients is looking for a Data Architect.




 You will join an international team of first-class professionals who are passionate about creating products that improve the quality of medical services.




 The company offers exposure to a variety of industries and technologies, room to grow as a professional, time in projects to learn new skills and an opportunity to work with phenomenal coworkers, some of the best people on the planet.




 Data Architect is supervising the data management and data governance practices across the data projects for the Cloud-native medical platform.




**Fundamentals:**
* 2+ years of experience with GCP Data Services (BQ, Spanner, Dataflow, Composer);
* Extensive OLTP and OLAP experience in terms of both SQL and Data Architecture;
* Ability to provide guidelines on DWH/LakeHouse Data Modeling both for Batching and Streaming architectures. DWH/LakeHouse Modeling with a robust, fast, distributed, and modern architecture;
* Understanding of Dimensional Modeling and SCD;
* Good understanding of data governance practices (DQ, data lineage, data stewardship);
* Extensive experience in leading whiteboarding sessions (Lucid, MS Visio);
* Strong leadership and negotiation skills: adept at driving change through influence and effective networking.


**Pros:**
* Experience in the Healthcare business domain;
* Good understanding of HIPAA Compliance;
* Experience with Enterprise Data Modeling (Data Vault, Inmon);
* Experience with Data Mesh;
* Experience with data contracts;
* Understanding of the Enterprise Architecture Frameworks (CSVLOD, TOGAF);
* Experience with Python.


**Limitations:**
* Ability to solve a couple of SQL problems in our live coding interview;
* Ability to build an e2e data platform in GCP given constraints and business priorities;
* Ability to work up to 13-14 EST. Probably, any Asian Time Zone is not acceptable at all.


**Technical Stack:**
* GCP in general
* GCP Cloud Build
* OLTP: Google Cloud Spanner
* OLAP: Google Cloud BigQuery, BigLake
* Google Kubernetes Engine
* DataFlow
* Python
* Cloud Composer
* Looker Studio
* Google Pub/Sub


**Benefits:**
* Flexible working hours;
* Remote work;
* Interesting projects to work on;
* Exposure to a variety of industries and technologies.
